We are a global information technology company that builds high-performance, security-centric solutions that can help change the world. Enhancing people’s lives through secure, reliable advanced technology is our vision.
At Unisys, we believe in better!
Here, you have the opportunity to learn new skills, apply your expertise, and solve complex problems with cutting-edge technologies and solutions. You are part of a globally diverse team that supports you, drives change, and delivers successful results consistently.
Our client, a prestigious European Agency, is looking for an Enterprise Architect to be
present on-site at the client offices in Strasbourg
and provide their expertise in enterprise systems design, operations, and large-scale distributed systems design and implementation.
Responsibilities
Support the design, development, implementation and maintenance of enterprise architecture;
Work with developers, product managers, business analysts, and subject matter experts to define solutions and modules with required features and functionalities;
Recommend and participate in the development of architecture blueprints;
Review the architecture of existing systems, design of component architecture, and building blocks;
Analyse the need for integration with different information Systems, e.g. Eurojust tools.;
Coordinate the design of the technical architectures and provide guidance on the design and implementation of the Service Oriented Architecture (SOA), Master Data Management (MDM) or other architecture methods;
Understands and apply security policy, measures, current standards, practices, and technology;
Work towards evolving the enterprise architecture by implementing the best practices, lessons learned and constantly updating the technical system architecture requirements based on changing technologies, and knowledge related to recent, current and up-coming vendor products and solutions.
Qualifications
Experience in translating organisational business process designs of multiple stakeholders into common collaboration design specifications;
Extensive knowledge and experience of architecture frameworks and methods and their practical implementation, working in an architecture role preferably within large companies, consultancy, or an enterprise software vendor;
Experience of working with a range of stakeholders to translate business and non-functional requirements into technology solutions;
In depth knowledge of interoperability frameworks, patterns and technologies;
Experience of devising architecture strategy to support future business goals;
Experience of defining roadmaps, current/future state models and maintaining architecture documentation;
Demonstrating extensive knowledge of enterprise systems design and operation in multi-national multi-platform environments;
Broad exposure/experience across service oriented systems design, contemporary web channel solutions, large scale distributed systems design and implementation;
Experience of on premise, virtualization and cloud-based Infrastructure (IaaS, PaaS, SaaS);
Experience of working in an agile software development environment;
Strong knowledge of cloud platforms;
Knowledge of security best practices and tools;
Capacity in writing and presenting documents;
Excellent communication skills;
Experience and willingness of working in an international/multicultural environment;
Affiliation with the European legal domain in order to understand legislative text and elaborate on that with the practitioners / subject matter experts involved in the procedure governed by that legal base;
Knowledge of requirements management tools: Reuse and Enterprise Architect preferably.
